benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: Valid payload scenarios across multiple TC tests (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC15) demonstrate successful blocking with HTTP 201 and a BlockingState array.
Comprehensive error handling and validation: tests cover 400 and 404 responses for invalid bundleId, non-existent bundle, missing or malformed request body/date format (TC06, TC07, TC08, TC10, TC11).
Authorization and authentication paths exercised: missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header and invalid token are covered (TC09, TC18).
Header and query parameter coverage includes required and optional headers/params, plus extra parameters (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC04).
Boundary and data validation scenarios are exercised: maximum/minimum BlockingState values, partial input, injection/XSS resilience (TC13, TC14, TC15, TC19, TC20).

Resilience, integration and reliability scenarios included: service unavailability (TC17), dependent service errors (TC28), cross-system data consistency (TC29), and accessibility of documentation (TC30).
Performance and scaling tests included: normal/peak load response times and resource utilization (TC25, TC26, TC27).
Regression coverage for special characters and backward compatibility (TC23, TC24).
gaps: Duplicate submission handling is not explicitly tested (idempotency behavior).
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios under burst traffic are not covered.
Caching behavior and validation of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) for POST responses are not tested.
recommendations: Add a dedicated test for duplicate submissions to verify idempotence and handling of repeated POST requests.
Add rate limiting tests to ensure server gracefully handles bursts and enforces quotas.
Add tests validating caching headers on POST responses if applicable, and verify client-side caching behavior.
Introduce tests for more granular authorization scenarios (e.g., insufficient permissions leading to 403).
Add explicit tests for extra body fields and ensure no injection/unknown fields leak into response (if necessary).
Consider tests to verify data consistency across systems in more complex integration scenarios.
